      "description": "Presenting a mechanically robust 2002 BMW M3 (E46) in driver-grade condition. This S54-powered icon features a high-revving 3.2L straight-six with individual throttle bodies, delivering linear power through a precise 6-speed manual transmission. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive VANOS service and subframe reinforcement. The chassis remains taut thanks to refreshed control arm bushings and a factory-spec limited-slip differential. While showing minor cosmetic patina from spirited use, the drivetrain remains potent and the throttle response is telepathic. An ideal acquisition for the purist seeking performance over concours perfection.",
